        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> and configure `vim.lsp.enable()` for various file formats separately in the `ftplugin` path because I don't want to enable all LSP configurations indiscriminately for all file formats. The problem I encountered was that `vim.lsp.enable()` was ineffective.\r\n\r\nI suspect that placing the vim.lsp.enable() call inside ftplugin prevents the LSP from attaching because it uses a FileType autocmd internally. That autocmd has to be created before the file is opened, but in your case it is only created after the file is already open and ftplugin has been executed.\r\n\r\nIt is fine to call vim.lsp.enable() for all servers in init.lua, because it only enables automatic attachment based on filetype - it does not start all servers indiscriminately.",
